Tip: Usually you only want to run wood in a single direction on the router table to prevent the issue you experienced.  Note the rotation of the bit and only move the wood in the direction that makes the bit push the wood into the fence.  If you go the other way, it will push the work away from the fence and then you don't get a nice slot like you wanted.  Also, table top router tables do exist and aren't terribly expensive.

The phenomenon that allows the hovercraft to hover like that is called "ground effect"..  Planes/helicopters  experience increased lift at aproximately one wingspan or less away from the ground, based on the resistance of the air being pushed down by the wing itself.  Planes can fly slower in ground effect because of the increased lift.
